    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="787"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.59A11/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Icelandic Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jonasson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reykjavik</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-15">April 15,
                            1940</date>.<lb/>[Received April 15—8:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of the status of Iceland created by parliamentary resolutions of April
                    10th, already notified to you, the Icelandic Government propose to establish a
                    Legation in Washington and at the same time to appoint consular representative
                    in New York. With this object in view they intend to appoint Mr. Vilhjalmur
                    Thor, Icelandic Government <pb facs="0685" n="676" xml:id="pg_676"/> Trade
                    Commissioner in New York and temporary Consul General for Iceland in New York;
                    to entrust him to be in charge of the Legation in Washington. Icelandic
                    Government would be glad to learn by telegram whether this proposed appointment
                    of Mr. Vilhjalmur [Thor] as Consul General for Iceland in New York and in charge
                    of Legation in Washington would be acceptable to the United States
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hermann Jonasson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
